@Jg1255 , I think we still want the `_claim_one_partition` method, which catches/deals with different exceptions with logging, here instead of going straight to `_update_ownership`. Otherwise, we would change/lose the behavior of this method when those exceptions occur.
I think I was unclear when I mentioned that there was a bug, sorry about that :P 

To be more clear, [here is a draft PR](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/pull/20008) with my changes of how this would look. (I still need to test these changes, just haven't had a chance to do that yet.) The biggest thing to note here is that we create a deep copy of the `ownership` dict in `_claim_one_partition` and pass that around, rather than modifying the original.

